
<h4>
  Nuclear Reaction Laws
</h4>

<p>
  When a nucleus decays,
  we draw a reaction with an arrow
  like this:
  $$
  ^{14} _6 \text{C} \longrightarrow ^{10} _4 \text{Be} + ^4 _2 \text{He}
  $$
</p>

<p class = 'definition' data-word = 'Conservation of Mass'>
  The mass numbers of the reactants and producs must add up.
  <br>
  <br>
  In the example above 14 = 10 + 4
</p>
<p class = 'definition' data-word = 'Conservation of Charge'>
  The atomic numbers (which represent charge) of the reactants
  and products must add up.
  <br><br>
  In the example above
  6 = 4 + 2
</p>

